   { title: 'Annual Limit', amount: '$3200' },
 ]}
/>

  <!-- FAQs Widget ******************* -->

  <FAQs
  title="Frequently Asked Questions about Energy Efficient Home Improvement Credit"
  items={[
    {
      title: 'What Is the Energy Efficient Home Improvement Credit (25C)?',
      description: 'The Energy Efficient Home Improvement Credit is a tax credit that provides financial incentives for homeowners to make energy-efficient upgrades to their residential properties. The credit covers a range of improvements, from insulation to energy-efficient windows and doors.',
    },
    {
      title: 'What Qualifies for the Energy Efficient Home Improvement Credit?',
      description: 'Eligible improvements include insulation systems, exterior windows, skylights, doors, and certain energy-efficient appliances like heat pumps and water heaters. The credit has been expanded to cover certain biomass stoves and boilers, electric panels, and home energy audits.',
    },
    {
      title: 'What Is the Annual Limit of the Energy Efficient Home Improvement Credit (25C)?',
      description: 'The annual limit for the 25C credit has been updated. Starting from January 1, 2023, you may qualify for a tax credit up to $3,200. This is a significant change from the previous lifetime limit of $500.',
    },
    {
      title: 'What Is the Difference Between 25C and HEEHRA?',
      description: 'The 25C credit, also known as the Energy Efficient Home Improvement Credit, focuses on a variety of home improvements like insulation and windows. HEEHRA (High Efficiency Electric Home Rebate Act) is a voluntary program that provides point-of-sale rebates for electrification projects, covering up to 100% of the costs for low-income households and 50% for moderate-income households.',
    },
    {
      title: 'How Do I Know My Eligibility for The Energy Efficient Home Improvement Credit?',
      description: 'To be eligible for the Energy Efficient Home Improvement Credit, you must make qualified energy-efficient improvements to your home after January 1, 2023. These improvements can include insulation systems, exterior windows, and certain energy-efficient appliances. The credit is available through 2032. For a more personalized assessment, you can use our [IRA Eligibility Calculator](#placeholder).',
    },
    {
      title: 'Is there a rollover with th Energy Efficient Home Improvement Credit?',
      description: 'Under 25c a taxpayer may not carry the credit forward. Thus, if a taxpayer does not have sufficient tax liability to claim all or a portion of the credit in the year in which therelated property for which the qualifying expenditure is placed in service, the unused amount of the credit may never be claimed.',
    }
  ]}
>
  <Fragment slot="bg">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-transparent"></div>
  </Fragment>

